description:
New Years Eve Sleep in party LATER START TIME. The self-care of sleeping in lives on. This week we are hitting the hilly upper woodlands gravel hill for some longer hilly tempos with ups and downs. The goal of this workout is to focus on a threshold effort while helping strengthen our quads to minimize muscle breakdown from downhill running. See the map on Slack for a visual of the route. This is a time and distance based werkout meant for all ability levels.

Meetup: Lower Woodland Soccer Parking, 5000 West Green Lake Way N, Seattle, WA 98103

 A group will leave for a warm up at 10:30am, start drills + strides at 10:50, and werkout starts at 11am.

Werkout:
2 mi warm up
form drills + strides
.63 miles, 8 RPE, 10k effort. (start at base of gravel hill, go all the way up to the top, take a right over the rolling gravel road of upper lower woodland, take a hard right to rejoin the original route and back up to the top.
3 min, easy jog/recovery back to bottom of gravel hill
Repeat x4-6
2 mi cooldown

Please RSVP if you plan on joining.
